{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> παύω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.67, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> παύεσκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.315, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 963 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> παύσω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.207, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>infinitive</i> παυσέμεν (κατα-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7.36: \">Refs</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἔπαυσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 15.15, etc.\">Refs</a>], <i>Epic dialect</i> παῦσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 17.602 \">Refs</a>]: <i>perfect</i> πέπαυκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.70, 4th c.BC: Antisthenes Rhetor “Ὀδυσσεύς” 10 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i> and <i>passive</i>, <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> παυέσκετο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.17 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> παύσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.198, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.56, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1040, “Ph.” 1424, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 93, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πεπαύσομαι only [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 91, “Tr.” 587 (though held to be the true _Attic dialect_ form by Moer. p.293 P.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; παυσθήσομαι (variant παυθ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.81 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; later παήσομαι (ἀνα-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Rev.14.13 \">NT</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐπαυσάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.260 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπαύθην, <i>Epic dialect</i> παύθην, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 533, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.91 (variant{παυσθῇ})\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], etc.; ἐπαύσθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.94, etc.; later ἐπάην 4th-5th c.AD: Choeroboscus Grammaticus “Scholia in Theodosii Canones” 2.141 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] H.: <i>perfect</i> πέπαυμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.125, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 615, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.84, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 29, etc. (πεπάσθαι is _falsa lectio_ in Vett. Val. 359.31): \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> causal, <b>make to end</b>, <br /><Level3><b>__I.1</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> only, <b>bring to an end, check</b>, sometimes of persons, ἵνα παύσομεν ἄγριον ἄνδρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.314, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 963 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 330 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>stop</b> or <b>silence</b> by death, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.274, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 397 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i> and <i>middle</i>, <b>take one's rest</b>, ἐνὶ κλισίῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.17, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.52, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>cease, have done</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.295, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.103, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of one singing or speaking, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 17.359, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.8.δ\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: generally, <i>middle</i> denotes <b>willing</b>, <i>passive</i> <b>forced, cessation.</b> <br /><Level4><b>__I.1.b</b></Level4> mostly of things, <b>make an end of, stop, abate</b>, χόλον, μένος, νεῖκος πολέμοιο, ῥόον, ὀδύνας, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.67, 1.282, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.543, 5.451, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.528, etc.; μέριμναν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).13 (assuming variant) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; λύπας ᾠδαῖς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 197 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.; π. τόξον <b>let</b> the bow <b>rest</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.279; π. τοὺς γάμους 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 575; πόντου σάλον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 1242 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. τὸν νόμον <b>annul</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Or.” 571 \">Refs</a>]; π. τὸν λόγον <b>close</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.6.7; τυραννίδα καταλύσαντα πεπαυκέναι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.70 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. τείχη <b>raze</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 69.9 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.91, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>person</i> et <i>genitive</i> <i>of things</i>, <b>hinder, keep back</b>, or <b>give</b> one <b>rest, from</b> a thing, π. Ἕκτορα μάχης, πόνοιο Ἀχιλῆα, Θάμυριν ἀοιδῆς, Πηνελόπειαν κλαυθμοῖο, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.15, 21.137, 2.595, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.801 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. τινὰ ἀλκῆς, ἄλης, καμάτοιο, ὀδυνάων, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.250, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.342, 5.492, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.191; so π. χεῖρας πολέμοιο 21.294; ὀρχηθμοῖο πόδας 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 23.298; π. τινὰ τῆς βοῆς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 798; τῆς ὕβρεως 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1259; τῆς λυγγός 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 185d \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τῆς ἁμαρτίας καὶ ἀμα θίας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lg.” 784c; τῶν ἐπιθυμιῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.2.5 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; [τῆς νόσου] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 42(1).121.71 (Epid., 4th c.BC) \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; π. τινὰ τῆς βασιληΐης <b>depose</b> one <b>from</b> being king, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.123 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τινὰ τῆς ἀρχῆς, τῆς στρατηγίας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.6.3, “HG” 6.2.13; τῆς ἔξω ξυμμαχίας τινάς 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.65; also π. τινὰ ἐκ κακῶν 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 987; τινὰ ἀπὸ παιδαγωγῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Respublica Lacedaemoniorum” 3.1; with _accusative_ unexpressed, αἴ κέ ποθι Ζεὺς.. παύσῃ ὀϊζύος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.35; φάρμαχ᾽ ἅ κεν παύσῃσι.. ὀδυνάων 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.191 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i> and <i>middle</i>, <b>rest</b> or <b>cease from</b> a thing, πολέμοιο, μάχης, ἔργων, πόνου, γόοιο, κλαυθμοῦ, ὀδυνάων, κλαγγῆς, etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.432, 467, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.683, 24.384, 9.540, 17.7, 4.812, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.100, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τῆς μάχης, τοῦ δρόμου, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.74, 4.124; γόων 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1211; τῆς ὀργῆς 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 19.6; φιλανθρώπου τρόπου 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 11 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; παύεσθαι ἀρχῆς <b>to be deposed from</b>, or <b>reach the term of</b>, office, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.56, compare 6.66, “IG” 12.114.46; ἐκ μεγάλων ἀχέων παυσαίμεθ᾽ ἄν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1531 (Lyric poetry); ἐκ τρόχων πεπαυμένοι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 46, compare “El.” 1108. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> with <i>present</i> <i>participle</i>, <b>stop</b> a person <b>from</b>.., π. τινὰ ἀριστεύοντα <b>stop</b> him <b>from</b> doing bravely, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.506; τὸν ἄνδρα παῦσον ταῦτα ποιεῦντα 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.23 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; γελῶντας ἐχθροὺς π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 1295; παύσω δέ σ᾽ ὄντ᾽ ἄπαιδα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 717 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i> and <i>middle</i>, <b>leave off doing</b>.., ὅθ᾽ ὕπνος ἕλοι, παύσαιτό τε νηπιαχεύων when <b>he stopped</b> playing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.502, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 615, “Ag.” 1047, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.133, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of things, ἄνεμος μὲν ἐπαύσατο.. θύων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.400: the \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>participle</i> is frequently to be supplied, αἷμα, φλόξ, ἄνεμος ἐπαύσατο, the blood <b>stopped</b> [flowing], the fire [burning], the wind [blowing], [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.267, 23.228, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.168, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; so Ῥοδώπιος πέρι πέπαυμαι (i.e. λέγων) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.135, compare 7.10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.4</b></Level3> less frequently with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>stop</b> a person <b>from</b>.., ἔμ᾽ ἔπαυσας ἐπὶ Τρώεσσι μάχεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.442; ῥαψῳδοὺς ἔπαυσε ἀγωνίζεσθαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.67, compare 7.54: sometimes with μή\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] inserted, θνητούς γ᾽ ἔπαυσα μὴ προδέρκεσθαι μόρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 250; παύσας ὑμᾶς μὴ λίαν ἐξαπατᾶσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 634; also π. τὸ μὴ προσελθεῖν.. τὴν ὁλκάδα 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.53; π. τοῦ.. εἶναι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 416c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__I.4.b</b></Level4> <i>middle</i> with <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Batrachomyomachia 193, “Anthologia Graeca” 6.21.8, and later Prose, as 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.216d. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.5</b></Level3> <i>middle</i>, <b>yield, give</b>, of timber, opposed to ἵστασθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 5.6.3. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>intransitive</i> in <i>imperative</i> παῦε, <b>cease, leave off</b> (παύου is rare, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 359, 4th c.BC: Ephippus Comicus 5.20, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Im.” 2), παῦε μάχης 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 449 codices, compare “hymnus ad Cererem” 351; παῦε γόοιο “epigram Gr.” 320.5 (from Thyatira): mostly _absolutely_, παῦε\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>stop! have done! be quiet!</b> παῦε, μὴ λέξῃς πέρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1275, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1208, “Ra.” 122, 269, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 228e; παῦε, παῦε, μὴ βόα 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1504, compare “V.” 1194; also παῦε, παῦε τοῦ λόγου [prev. author] “Ra.” 580; παῦε, παῦ᾽ ὀρχούμενος [prev. author] “Pax” 326; παῦ᾽ ἐς κόρακας [prev. author] “Ach.” 864 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], where the other Verbs are <i>plural</i>; παῦ, <i>apocalyptic</i> for παῦε, παῦ, μηδὲν ὄμνυ᾽ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Σαμία” 96, compare 2nd c.AD: Aelius Dionysius Grammaticus “fragment” 275, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: also <i>imperative</i> <i>middle</i>, παῦσαι λέγουσα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 706; παῦσαι φαρμακοπωλῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 28; π. μελῳδοῦσ᾽ “Comica Adespota” 601; π. δυσωνῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 224, compare 5th c.BC: Theopompus Comicus 62, {5-6th c.BC}: Philetaerus Comicus 6, 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 213.1 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; παύσασθε νοῦν ἔχοντες (to be read λέγοντες) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 482.1. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3973","accentedUnicode":"παύω","shortDef":"(act.) to cause to stop; (<i>middle</i>) to stop, cease, finish","mediumDef":"(act.) to cause to stop; (<i>middle</i>) to stop, cease, finish <br /><b>to cause to pause</b>, or <b>cease, restrain, prohibit,</b> <ref='1Pe.3.10'>1Pet. 3:10;</ref> <i>middle</i> <i>perfect</i> <greek>πέπαυται</greek>, <b>to cease, stop, leave off, desist, refrain,</b> <ref='1Pe.4.1'>1Pet. 4:1</ref>","stepGloss":"to cease","stepTransliteration":"pauō","count":15,"_es_Definition":"parar, impedir (1PE.3:10) ; voz media: detener, suspender, cesar ; cesar de, terminar con","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 使停息或停止 #彼前 3:10|<br>2) (自己) 停止, 中止 (作某件事)","_zh_Definition":"1) 使停息或停止 #彼前 3:10|<br>2) (自己) 停止, 中止 (作某件事)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"ngừng, tạm nghỉ; dừng lại, kết thúc; bỏ; kết thúc; rời bỏ; tống khứ; chấm dứt.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"住","_es_Gloss":"cesar","_zh_Gloss":"住"}]}